# 20. needLe

Honami: Saki... Shiho...
Honami: Please forgive me!
Honami: When my classmates started ignoring me, I was terrified. But I couldn't bring myself to tell you what was going on.
Honami: I was so afraid it would happen again in high school, so I did everything I could not to upset the few people in my class who were nice to me.
Honami: I acted as if you weren't my friends any more, even though that hurt you...
Ichika: Honami...
Honami: It all happened because I'm so spineless...
Saki: You're not. I should apologize for not having been able to help you.
Saki: I wasn't there for you when you were having a really difficult time.
Ichika: I also shouldn't have left you alone for so long. I noticed that something was wrong, but did nothing.
Honami: How can you still care about me after I shunned everyone and hurt your feelings...
Shiho: It's simple. You're our friend.
Shiho: I'm sorry about what I said earlier.
Honami: Shiho...
Honami: No, you were right. You opened my eyes to what I was doing to all of you.
Honami: If you hadn't gotten so angry with me, I'd have just carried on, telling myself everything was all right.
Honami: Thank you, Shiho.
Shiho: Honami...
Saki: *Sob*... Haha, your eyes are red from crying, guys.
Ichika: You should take a look in the mirror.
Shiho: I wasn't crying...
Ichika: Honami.
Ichika: Join our band.
Ichika: We won't leave you alone ever again. We'll always be together.
Honami: Sure. Thank you, everyone.
Saki: Hehehe! At last we're a band of four!
Shiho: Honami, our band's no joke. You've got to be serious about practice.
Saki: Yikes! Shiho's already putting the pressure on!
Shiho: What? I'm just making it clear that if we're doing this together, we've got to do it right.
Honami: Hehe.
Ichika: What is it, Honami?
Honami: I'm just so happy that I'll be in a band with you.
Honami: I think this is what I wanted right from the start.
Ichika: Honami...
Miku: You've finally discovered your true feelings.
Ichika: Oh? My phone flashed?
Saki: Huh? Why are we back in the classroom?
Luka: Your feelings are about to turn into a song.
Luka: Honami, you're a part of it too.
Honami: I see. I, um...
Honami: I'm very grateful to you, Luka and Miku. For showing us that wonderful starry sky.
Miku: You know what comes next, right?
Saki: Yeah! We're gonna to play together!
Shiho: Okay. Which song?
Saki: Whoa! My phone's doing it again!
Saki: Wait, no... It's just Untitled that's flashing?
Ichika: It's doing it on my phone too!
Miku: Your feelings are becoming a song. Would you mind if I sang with you?
Ichika: We'd love you to, Miku.
Ichika: It's also your song. We wouldn't have discovered it if it weren't for you and Luka.
Luka: Hehe, thanks. I suppose I'll join in too then.
Miku: Ichika, let's sing together!
Ichika: We played as if we'd known this song for a long time.
Saki: That was awesome... So freaking awesome! Like, super awesome!
Shiho: I guess if this song expresses our feelings, then they're feelings we've all shared since a long time ago.
Honami: Yeah, I felt that too. It was so familiar and feel-good.
Ichika: Look... The song's name is changing.
Saki: Now it's called needLe?
Miku: Your feelings have crystallized into a song at last.
Shiho: So there's a part of each of us...
Honami: ...in this song.
Ichika: So this song is needLe, huh. We'll treasure it.
